»IN LOVING MEMORY
ALLAN ASHFIELD

A MUCH LOVED DAD, HUSBAND AND FRIEND TO
US ALL, SADLY MISSED
He walked his dog Bazil, and loved to come fishing here.
"TIGHT LINES MATE""─
┴A GOOD NAME IS RATHER TO BE CHOSEN THAN GREAT RICHES AND LOVING FAVOUR RATHER THAN SILVER AND GOLD
PROVERBS 22 CHAPTER 1

THANKS BE TO GOD
FOR THE SACRED REMEMBRANCE OF
MY BELOVED HUSBAND
SIDNEY JOHN FIELD
A FRIEND OF NORTON LINDSEY
AND A LOVER OF THE
SURROUNDING COUNTRY
TO KEEP HIS MEMORY GREEN
FEBRUARY 1934"¾
